body:
When I use the following `sync.yml`

```json
{
   "docker.io": {
     "images": {
         "haproxy": [
            "sha256:8721b6ad811d2f478b7b3de6c4bb5d4f077b3ab8f2e7a24a29e32c35a894bfd9"
         ]
      }
   }
}
```

with the command

```bash
skopeo sync --preserve-digests  --override-arch amd64 --override-os linux --digestfile sync_digest.txt  --src yaml --dest docker --scoped sync.yml example.com/sync_with_digest
```

the command succeeds. However, the digest of copied artifact has not been preserved (which is expected, because of the override options). This is visible in the digestfile:

```
sha256:8a304a313c511a003342fc32f1afc40f211ad4c7f1f90a1decbc3d365ceb3125 docker://example.com/sync_with_digest/docker.io/library/haproxy@sha256:8721b6ad811d2f478b7b3de6c4bb5d4f077b3ab8f2e7a24a29e32c35a894bfd9
```

From the documentation, I would expect that the command fails, because it cannot preserve the digest in that situation.

I am on version 1.20.0

